<emphasis id="B917EA88FF81FFEEFF6FFC48FEAE2565" bold="true" box="[145,265,1023,1045]" pageId="52" pageNumber="637">Figure 39.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C634D19FF81FFEEFEEAFBB7FDB42564" authorityName="Medrano &amp; Kury &amp; Mendes" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Roewer" baseAuthorityYear="1947" box="[276,531,1023,1045]" class="Arachnida" family="Cosmetidae" genus="Protus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opiliones" pageId="52" pageNumber="637" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadripunctatus">
<emphasis id="B917EA88FF81FFEEFEEAFBB7FDB42564" box="[276,531,1023,1045]" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="637">Protus quadripunctatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, male syntype (SMF RII 1489/7a). A, dorsal view. B, ventral view. C, lateral view. D, detail of coxa IV in dorsal view. E, original label. Scale bars: 1 mm. Photos courtesy Abel Pérez.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<caption id="DF1C6612FF81FFEEFF6FF8F5FA352628" box="[145,1426,1858,1881]" pageId="52" pageNumber="637" startId="52.[145,223,1858,1880]" targetBox="[305,1265,1102,1819]" targetPageId="52">
<paragraph id="8BDC369AFF81FFEEFF6FF8F5FA352628" blockId="52.[145,1426,1858,1881]" box="[145,1426,1858,1881]" pageId="52" pageNumber="637">
<emphasis id="B917EA88FF81FFEEFF6FF8F5FEA12626" bold="true" box="[145,262,1858,1880]" pageId="52" pageNumber="637">Figure 40.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C634D19FF81FFEEFEEEF8F4FE1D2628" authorityName="Medrano &amp; Kury &amp; Mendes" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Roewer" baseAuthorityYear="1928" box="[272,442,1859,1881]" class="Arachnida" family="Cosmetidae" genus="Protus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opiliones" pageId="52" pageNumber="637" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="speciosus">
<emphasis id="B917EA88FF81FFEEFEEEF8F4FE1D2628" box="[272,442,1859,1881]" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="637">Protus speciosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, male (ICN-Ao-381). A, dorsal view. B, lateral view. C, panoramic dorsal view. Scale bars: 1 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<caption id="DF1C6612FF80FFEFFF5DF934FADE27A5" pageId="53" pageNumber="638" startId="53.[163,242,1667,1689]" targetBox="[163,1443,196,1626]" targetPageId="53">
<paragraph id="8BDC369AFF80FFEFFF5DF934FADE27A5" blockId="53.[163,1443,1667,1748]" pageId="53" pageNumber="638">
<emphasis id="B917EA88FF80FFEFFF5DF934FEBE27E9" bold="true" box="[163,281,1667,1689]" pageId="53" pageNumber="638">Figure 41.</emphasis>
SEM images of some structures of 
<taxonomicName id="4C634D19FF80FFEFFD6DF933FC9827E8" authorityName="Medrano &amp; Kury &amp; Mendes" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Roewer" baseAuthorityYear="1928" box="[659,831,1667,1689]" class="Arachnida" family="Cosmetidae" genus="Protus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opiliones" pageId="53" pageNumber="638" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="speciosus">
<emphasis id="B917EA88FF80FFEFFD6DF933FC9827E8" box="[659,831,1667,1689]" italics="true" pageId="53" pageNumber="638">Protus speciosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, male (ICN-Ao- 467). A–C, penis: A, dorsal view; B, lateral view; C, ventral view. D, left cheliceral hand, frontal view. E, left basichelicerite, dorsal view. F, left pedipalpus, mesal view. G, same, dorsal view. H, same, detail of tarsus, ventral view. Scale bars: 100 μm (A–C, E, H), 200 μm (D), 500 μm (F, G).
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BDC369AFF83FFECFF6FFC3FFF5725E3" blockId="54.[145,762,904,1170]" pageId="54" pageNumber="639">
<emphasis id="B917EA88FF83FFECFF6FFC3FFEBD22EC" box="[145,282,904,925]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="639">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
May be differentiated from other 
<taxonomicName id="4C634D19FF83FFECFF6FFC10FF7922CD" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1879" box="[145,222,935,956]" class="Arachnida" family="Cosmetidae" genus="Protus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opiliones" pageId="54" pageNumber="639" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B917EA88FF83FFECFF6FFC10FF7922CD" box="[145,222,935,956]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="639">Protus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the combination of the following features: lateral margins of DS with a yellow stripe going from carapace to area 
<collectionCode id="ED72AE5FFF83FFECFE5BFC53FE652288" box="[421,450,996,1017]" pageId="54" pageNumber="639">IV</collectionCode>
in abdomen, but without invading mesotergum (
<figureCitation id="13582A1FFF83FFECFE52FBB5FDB52566" box="[428,530,1026,1048]" captionStart="Figure 40" captionStartId="52.[145,223,1858,1880]" captionTargetBox="[305,1265,1102,1819]" captionTargetId="figure-25@52.[305,1265,1102,1819]" captionTargetPageId="52" captionText="Figure 40. Protus speciosus, male (ICN-Ao-381).A, dorsal view. B, lateral view. C, panoramic dorsal view. Scale bars: 1 mm." pageId="54" pageNumber="639">Fig. 40A</figureCitation>
); coxa 
<collectionCode id="ED72AE5FFF83FFECFD97FBB4FD212569" box="[617,646,1027,1048]" pageId="54" pageNumber="639">IV</collectionCode>
with one yellow dot in lateral side (
<figureCitation id="13582A1FFF83FFECFE27FB96FDE72547" box="[473,576,1057,1079]" captionStart="Figure 40" captionStartId="52.[145,223,1858,1880]" captionTargetBox="[305,1265,1102,1819]" captionTargetId="figure-25@52.[305,1265,1102,1819]" captionTargetPageId="52" captionText="Figure 40. Protus speciosus, male (ICN-Ao-381).A, dorsal view. B, lateral view. C, panoramic dorsal view. Scale bars: 1 mm." pageId="54" pageNumber="639">Fig. 40B</figureCitation>
); distal border of 
<collectionCode id="ED72AE5FFF83FFECFF50FBF7FF762524" box="[174,209,1088,1109]" pageId="54" pageNumber="639">VP</collectionCode>
of the penis convex without median cleft and stylus with distal wattle not going to the base (
<figureCitation id="13582A1FFF83FFECFD32FBE9FF4725E3" captionStart="Figure 41" captionStartId="53.[163,242,1667,1689]" captionTargetBox="[163,1443,196,1626]" captionTargetId="figure-25@53.[163,1443,195,1627]" captionTargetPageId="53" captionText="Figure 41. SEM images of some structures of Protus speciosus, male (ICN-Ao- 467). A–C, penis: A, dorsal view; B, lateral view; C, ventral view. D, left cheliceral hand, frontal view. E, left basichelicerite, dorsal view. F, left pedipalpus, mesal view. G, same, dorsal view. H, same, detail of tarsus, ventral view. Scale bars: 100 μm (A–C, E, H), 200 μm (D), 500 μm (F, G)." pageId="54" pageNumber="639">Fig. 41A–C</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDC369AFF83FFECFF6FFB73FD632444" blockId="54.[145,760,1220,1334]" pageId="54" pageNumber="639">
<emphasis id="B917EA88FF83FFECFF6FFB73FE9025A8" box="[145,311,1220,1241]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="639">Distribution:</emphasis>
Solimões-Japurá moist forest in 
<collectingRegion id="49A7F878FF83FFECFF6FFB54FE122589" box="[145,437,1250,1272]" country="Colombia" name="Amazonas" pageId="54" pageNumber="639">Amazonas department</collectingRegion>
of 
<collectingCountry id="F374760AFF83FFECFE18FB55FDC62589" box="[486,609,1250,1272]" name="Colombia" pageId="54" pageNumber="639">Colombia</collectingCountry>
, Southwest Amazon moist forest and Japurá-Solimões-Negro moist forest in Amazonas state of 
<collectingCountry id="F374760AFF83FFECFDEDFA97FDFE2447" box="[531,601,1312,1334]" name="Brazil" pageId="54" pageNumber="639">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation id="13582A1FFF83FFECFD96FA97FD132444" box="[616,692,1312,1334]" captionStart="Figure 30" captionStartId="41.[163,241,928,950]" captionTargetBox="[165,1446,197,888]" captionTargetId="figure-513@41.[163,1446,195,889]" captionTargetPageId="41" captionText="Figure 30. Map of known distribution of Protus. Numbers correspond to the following WWF ecoregions: 1 = Ucayali moist forest, 2 = Iquitos varzea, 3 = Southwest Amazon moist forest, 4 = Solimões-Japurá moist forest, 5 = Juruá-Purus moist forest, 6 = Madeira-Tapajos moist forest, 7 = Japurá-Solimões-Negro moist forest, 8 = Uatuma-Trombetas moist forest, 9 = Mato Grosso seasonal forest." pageId="54" pageNumber="639">Fig. 30</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDC369AFF83FFECFF6FFAD3FD0E24C6" blockId="54.[145,762,1380,1892]" pageId="54" pageNumber="639">
<emphasis id="B917EA88FF83FFECFF6FFAD3FE3624E9" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="639">Description of male ICN-Ao-381 (with extra figures from other specimens):</emphasis>
Measurements: CL: 1.70, CW: 2.58, AL: 3.05, AW: 4.35, IOD: 0.72, FeIV: 14.62.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDC369AFF83FFECFF57FA77FE022679" blockId="54.[145,762,1380,1892]" pageId="54" pageNumber="639">
Dorsum (
<figureCitation id="13582A1FFF83FFECFEE4FA77FECB24A4" box="[282,364,1472,1494]" captionStart="Figure 40" captionStartId="52.[145,223,1858,1880]" captionTargetBox="[305,1265,1102,1819]" captionTargetId="figure-25@52.[305,1265,1102,1819]" captionTargetPageId="52" captionText="Figure 40. Protus speciosus, male (ICN-Ao-381).A, dorsal view. B, lateral view. C, panoramic dorsal view. Scale bars: 1 mm." pageId="54" pageNumber="639">Fig. 40</figureCitation>
). DS beta-type and lenticular in lateral view, without remarkable ornamentation, only low, coloured tubercles in areas I and 
<collectionCode id="ED72AE5FFF83FFECFDCBFA4AFDF22763" box="[565,597,1533,1554]" pageId="54" pageNumber="639">III</collectionCode>
. Anterior edge of dorsal scutum with protoglyphs slightly concave with lateral triangular borders. Ocularium low and with a few granules near the eyes. Mesotergum convex, higher at level of area 
<collectionCode id="ED72AE5FFF83FFECFE6AF9CFFE0E27FC" box="[404,425,1656,1677]" pageId="54" pageNumber="639">II</collectionCode>
, scutal areas I and 
<collectionCode id="ED72AE5FFF83FFECFD74F9CFFD0F27FC" box="[650,680,1656,1677]" pageId="54" pageNumber="639">III</collectionCode>
armed with a pair of rounded tubercles, other areas unarmed. Posterior border and free tergites each containing a transverse row of minute granules, anal operculum with scattered granules.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDC369AFF83FFECFF57F8A6FB722046" blockId="54.[145,762,1380,1892]" lastBlockId="54.[809,1426,197,1691]" pageId="54" pageNumber="639">
Venter. Coxae I– 
<collectionCode id="ED72AE5FFF83FFECFE93F8A6FE2C2657" box="[365,395,1809,1830]" pageId="54" pageNumber="639">III</collectionCode>
triangular, transverse to main body axis, each with a longitudinal row of granules. Coxae 
<collectionCode id="ED72AE5FFF83FFECFF1CF8F8FF522615" box="[226,245,1871,1892]" pageId="54" pageNumber="639">II</collectionCode>
– 
<collectionCode id="ED72AE5FFF83FFECFEFAF8F8FE852615" box="[260,290,1871,1892]" pageId="54" pageNumber="639">IV</collectionCode>
connected by tubercular bridges. Coxa 
<collectionCode id="ED72AE5FFF83FFECFCD7FF72FCE221AB" box="[809,837,197,218]" pageId="54" pageNumber="639">IV</collectionCode>
pentagonal, greatly developed, oriented obliquely, but almost parallel to the body axis. Stigmatic area T-shaped with stigmata large, unconcealed. Free sternites each with a row of granules.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDC369AFF83FFECFCBFFEF7FB70235D" blockId="54.[809,1426,197,1691]" pageId="54" pageNumber="639">
Chelicerae (
<figureCitation id="13582A1FFF83FFECFC1BFEF7FBDA2024" box="[997,1149,320,342]" captionStart="Figure 41" captionStartId="53.[163,242,1667,1689]" captionTargetBox="[163,1443,196,1626]" captionTargetId="figure-25@53.[163,1443,195,1627]" captionTargetPageId="53" captionText="Figure 41. SEM images of some structures of Protus speciosus, male (ICN-Ao- 467). A–C, penis: A, dorsal view; B, lateral view; C, ventral view. D, left cheliceral hand, frontal view. E, left basichelicerite, dorsal view. F, left pedipalpus, mesal view. G, same, dorsal view. H, same, detail of tarsus, ventral view. Scale bars: 100 μm (A–C, E, H), 200 μm (D), 500 μm (F, G)." pageId="54" pageNumber="639">Fig. 41D, E</figureCitation>
). Hand not swollen. Basichelicerite short, with well-marked bulla and uniformly granulated dorsally. Mesal margin of bulla with three setiferous tubercles, larger than dorsal ones. Posterior and ectal margins of bulla fringed with many tubercles. Movable finger of cheliceral hand with nine trapezoidal tubercles. Fixed finger with three triangular tubercles of different sizes.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDC369AFF83FFECFCBFFD82FA352250" blockId="54.[809,1426,197,1691]" pageId="54" pageNumber="639">
Pedipalps (
<figureCitation id="13582A1FFF83FFECFC2BFD82FBC1233B" box="[981,1126,565,587]" captionStart="Figure 41" captionStartId="53.[163,242,1667,1689]" captionTargetBox="[163,1443,196,1626]" captionTargetId="figure-25@53.[163,1443,195,1627]" captionTargetPageId="53" captionText="Figure 41. SEM images of some structures of Protus speciosus, male (ICN-Ao- 467). A–C, penis: A, dorsal view; B, lateral view; C, ventral view. D, left cheliceral hand, frontal view. E, left basichelicerite, dorsal view. F, left pedipalpus, mesal view. G, same, dorsal view. H, same, detail of tarsus, ventral view. Scale bars: 100 μm (A–C, E, H), 200 μm (D), 500 μm (F, G)." pageId="54" pageNumber="639">Fig. 41F–H</figureCitation>
). Elongate trochanter, foliaceus femur, convex dorsally, with a dorsal row of seven setiferous tubercles and a ventral row of 14 setiferous tubercles. Tibia only slightly convex in the mesal side, with two ventro-marginal rows of small setae each side, mesal region three equally spaced large setae. Tarsus conical, with scattered dorsal setae and three well-marked ventral rows of subequal setae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDC369AFF83FFECFCBFFC9CFBB422CB" blockId="54.[809,1426,197,1691]" pageId="54" pageNumber="639">
Legs (
<figureCitation id="13582A1FFF83FFECFC71FC9DFC42224E" box="[911,997,810,832]" captionStart="Figure 40" captionStartId="52.[145,223,1858,1880]" captionTargetBox="[305,1265,1102,1819]" captionTargetId="figure-25@52.[305,1265,1102,1819]" captionTargetPageId="52" captionText="Figure 40. Protus speciosus, male (ICN-Ao-381).A, dorsal view. B, lateral view. C, panoramic dorsal view. Scale bars: 1 mm." pageId="54" pageNumber="639">Fig. 40</figureCitation>
). Long and unarmed legs, femora straight. Coxa 
<collectionCode id="ED72AE5FFF83FFECFC31FCFEFC4C222F" box="[975,1003,841,862]" pageId="54" pageNumber="639">IV</collectionCode>
convex in dorsal view with few apical granules, no clavi inguines. Pectinate claws in legs 
<collectionCode id="ED72AE5FFF83FFECFA82FCDFFA37220C" box="[1404,1424,872,893]" pageId="54" pageNumber="639">II</collectionCode>
and 
<collectionCode id="ED72AE5FFF83FFECFCA4FC30FCD122ED" box="[858,886,903,924]" pageId="54" pageNumber="639">IV</collectionCode>
in two rows. Tarsal counts: 7(3), 15(3), 11, 12/13 (from 
<bibRefCitation id="EFF24B6BFF83FFECFC93FC12FBA322CB" author="Roewer CF" box="[877,1028,933,954]" pageId="54" pageNumber="639" pagination="527 - 632" refId="ref54532" refString="Roewer CF. 1928 [' 1927 ']. Weitere Weberknechte II. (2. Erganzung der Weberknechte der Erde, 1923). Abhandlungen der Naturwissenschaftlichen Verein zu Bremen 26: 527 - 632." type="journal article" year="1928">Roewer, 1928</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDC369AFF83FFECFCBFFC74FC4625BE" blockId="54.[809,1426,197,1691]" pageId="54" pageNumber="639">
Colour (in alcohol, 
<figureCitation id="13582A1FFF83FFECFBCDFC74FB2E22A8" box="[1075,1161,963,985]" captionStart="Figure 40" captionStartId="52.[145,223,1858,1880]" captionTargetBox="[305,1265,1102,1819]" captionTargetId="figure-25@52.[305,1265,1102,1819]" captionTargetPageId="52" captionText="Figure 40. Protus speciosus, male (ICN-Ao-381).A, dorsal view. B, lateral view. C, panoramic dorsal view. Scale bars: 1 mm." pageId="54" pageNumber="639">Fig. 40</figureCitation>
). DS and coxae dark reddish-brown (44), with numerous two lateral stripes and two paramedian spots brilliant greenish-yellow (98) in each area I and 
<collectionCode id="ED72AE5FFF83FFECFBB0FB97FBD62544" box="[1102,1137,1056,1077]" pageId="54" pageNumber="639">III</collectionCode>
. Coxa 
<collectionCode id="ED72AE5FFF83FFECFB3AFB97FB462544" box="[1220,1249,1056,1077]" pageId="54" pageNumber="639">IV</collectionCode>
with one spot of the same colour than stripes in DS. Trochanters vivid greenish-yellow (97) and the rest of podomeres brilliant yellow-green (116) and dark olive (108). Chelicerae and pedipalps deep orange (51) mottled in dark brown (59)
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDC369AFF83FFECFCBFFB60FB7E27EA" blockId="54.[809,1426,197,1691]" pageId="54" pageNumber="639">
Penis (
<figureCitation id="13582A1FFF83FFECFC65FB60FB8D259D" box="[923,1066,1239,1261]" captionStart="Figure 41" captionStartId="53.[163,242,1667,1689]" captionTargetBox="[163,1443,196,1626]" captionTargetId="figure-25@53.[163,1443,195,1627]" captionTargetPageId="53" captionText="Figure 41. SEM images of some structures of Protus speciosus, male (ICN-Ao- 467). A–C, penis: A, dorsal view; B, lateral view; C, ventral view. D, left cheliceral hand, frontal view. E, left basichelicerite, dorsal view. F, left pedipalpus, mesal view. G, same, dorsal view. H, same, detail of tarsus, ventral view. Scale bars: 100 μm (A–C, E, H), 200 μm (D), 500 μm (F, G)." pageId="54" pageNumber="639">Fig. 41A–C</figureCitation>
). Ventral plate rectangular elongate, with apical corners rounded, distal margin convex. Sub-distal lateral margin of 
<collectionCode id="ED72AE5FFF83FFECFB3AFAA2FB41245B" box="[1220,1254,1301,1322]" pageId="54" pageNumber="639">VP</collectionCode>
with two pairs of MS-C, large, slender and conical. Two pairs of 
<collectionCode id="ED72AE5FFF83FFECFAB1FA84FA362439" box="[1359,1425,1331,1352]" pageId="54" pageNumber="639">MS-D</collectionCode>
located in apical half of 
<collectionCode id="ED72AE5FFF83FFECFBBEFAE5FBC52416" box="[1088,1122,1362,1383]" pageId="54" pageNumber="639">VP</collectionCode>
, MS-D1 twice longer than MS-D2 and closer to MS-C2, both 
<collectionCode id="ED72AE5FFF83FFECFB48FAC6FB5E24F7" box="[1206,1273,1393,1414]" pageId="54" pageNumber="639">MS-D</collectionCode>
straight and conical. One pair of 
<collectionCode id="ED72AE5FFF83FFECFBDBFA38FBCE24D5" box="[1061,1129,1423,1444]" pageId="54" pageNumber="639">MS-A</collectionCode>
basally in 
<collectionCode id="ED72AE5FFF83FFECFB08FA27FABE24D4" box="[1270,1305,1424,1445]" pageId="54" pageNumber="639">VP</collectionCode>
, straight, conical and as long as MS-D1. Two pairs of MS-E in apical portion of lateroventral surface and one pair of MS-B in the basal portion of ventral surface of 
<collectionCode id="ED72AE5FFF83FFECFCD7F9BDFCEB276E" box="[809,844,1546,1567]" pageId="54" pageNumber="639">VP</collectionCode>
. Ventral surface glabrous apically, two wide basal regions with microsetae 
<typeStatus id="54D88838FF83FFECFBB1F99EFB25274F" box="[1103,1154,1577,1598]" pageId="54" pageNumber="639">type</typeStatus>
1 (T1) near MS-B and invading truncus. Glans with dorsal process thin and acuminate, stylus with a reduced distal wattle with serrate part and without stylar barbs.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
